    • Method Detail

      • cancelReservation

        org.w3c.dom.Document cancelReservation(YFSEnvironment env,
                                       org.w3c.dom.Document inXML)
                                throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,
                                       java.rmi.RemoteException

        The cancelReservation API removes an existing inventory reservation. Inventory reservation of components can be canceled using bundle parent.

        Related Documents
        Input XML Input DTD Output XML Output DTD Error XML Error DTD

        User Exits: com.yantra.ycm.japi.ue.YCMGetItemDetailsUE

        Events Raised:

        EXTERNAL_DEMAND_CHANGE
        Key Data: INVENTORY_CHANGE_EXTERNAL_DEMAND_CHANGE_dbd.txt
        Data Published: INV_INVENTORY_CHANGE.EXTERNAL_DEMAND_CHANGE.html

        RESERVATION_CHANGE
        Raised whenever reservation change occurs.
        Key Data: INVENTORY_CHANGE_RESERVATION_CHANGE_dbd.txt
        Data Published: INV_INVENTORY_CHANGE.RESERVATION_CHANGE.html

        CAPACITY_CHANGE.ON_STD_CAPACITY_FREED
        Raised when consumption is freed and standard capacity becomes available for the day.
        Data Published: INV_CAPACITY_CHANGE.ON_STD_CAPACITY_FREED.html
        Template Support: Yes
        Configuration Required for backward compatibility: No

        CAPACITY_CHANGE.EXTERNAL_CAPACITY_CHANGE
        This event is raised when capacity consumptions are changed.
        Data published: YFS_CAPACITY_CHANGE.EXTERNAL_CAPACITY_CHANGE.xml
        Template Support: Yes
        Configuration Required for backward compatibility: No

        Audits: None

        Pre-conditions: None

        Post-conditions: Reservations are cancelled.

        Output Template Support: No

        Database Extensibility Support: No

        *

        Additional Information:
        API throws error if availability is maintained externally for primary enterprise code of inventory organization or ShipNode.

        Parameters:
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API.
        inXML - Required. For more information, see the associated input xml files.

        Returns:
        An XML document that contains information on removing an existing reservation. For details on the output, refer to the associated output xml files.

        Throws:
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException - Exception containing error codes in the standard XML error and DTD error files.
        java.rmi.RemoteException - Java's default remote exception handler.
